    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-12-23T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-12-23T13:00:00-05:00" n="616"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d616">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">832.61333/12–2344: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Donnelly</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-12-23T15:00:00-03:00"
                            >December 23, 1944—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 7:01 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4521. Department’s 3764 December 22, 1 p.m.<note n="22" xml:id="d616fn22">Not
                        printed; it suggested the advisability of opening conversations to renew the
                        July Memorandum of Understanding (832.61333/12–2244).</note> The time is not
                    opportune, in my opinion, to discuss the matter with Souza Costa because he is
                    very disappointed over the results of the Vinson meeting (Department’s circular
                    telegram December 21, 10 p.m.<note n="23" xml:id="d616fn23">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_166">p. 166</ref>.</note>).
                    Moreover the new president of the National Coffee Department<note n="24"
                        xml:id="d616fn24">Ovidio de Abreu.</note> (Embassy’s 4474, December 8 [<hi
                        rend="italic">18</hi>], 6 p.m.<note n="25" xml:id="d616fn25">Not
                        printed.</note>)will take office on December 26 and this will be followed by
                    a reorganization of the Department and possibly changes in the coffee
                    policy.</p>
                <p>I told Souza Costa yesterday (and Velloso today) that there will be no increase
                    in coffee price ceilings. He remarked that politically <pb facs="0656" n="642"
                        xml:id="pg_642"/> the situation is very difficult for him. He said that
                    Penteado continues to send optimistic reports regarding the possibilities for
                    obtaining an increase in prices.</p>
                <p>I expect to meet next week with Souza Costa and the new president of the DNC and
                    shall inform the Department of their views on the coffee situation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Donnelly</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
